§431:10B-104    Credit life insurance and credit disability insurance shall be issued only in the following forms:



	(1)	Individual policies of life insurance issued to debtors on the term plan;
	(2)	Individual policies of accident and health or sickness insurance issued to debtors on a term plan or disability benefit provisions in individual policies of credit life insurance;
	(3)	Group policies of life insurance issued to creditors pursuant to section 431:10D-203 providing insurance upon the lives of debtors on the term plan; and
	(4)	Group policies of accident and health or sickness insurance issued to creditors on a term plan insuring debtors or disability benefit provisions in group credit life insurance policies to provide such coverage. [L 1987, c 347, pt of §2; am L 2003, c 212, §82]
